Boy oh boy oh boy. Where to begin...  I love Sweetgreen for the Hummus Tahina, but this location is consistently problematic. Hummus Tahina has been around at SG for as long as I can remember (since at least 2012ish). The recipe is also posted on their windows and the employee is clearly reading it as she mixes the salad. So when you forget the onions, no big deal. I'll remind you. And when you forget the feta, I'll again interject to remind you. And when you forget the falafel, I'll remind you. But...HOW do you forget the hummus???? It's baffling. Imagine if I had ordered online. I'd have had a ten dollar bowl of lettuce.  Another time, one employee was cleaning the counter as a line formed. We all waited patiently as she told us someone would be right with us. Five minutes later, nothing. Then she yells, "HEY!" to the two employees giggling down by the cash register and finally we get service. On the plus side, I watched her clean very thoroughly for those 5 minutes, so at least it's clean?

CARD ONLY!! Highly recommend those who has a vegetarian or vegan diet. This place is amazing in offering a large variety of locally source ingredients like their meat and vegetables. Most salad places do not have hot toppings/options you can add on to salads. Many of the flavors does comes from the food instead of the salad dressing I.e. sweet potato, curry cauliflower, Brussel sprout. The chicken is slightly dry as they use chicken breast. Despite it being dry, it is flavorful and well seasoned.  Once you walk, on the left consist of pick up orders. There are limited tables but plenty of seating area in forms of stairs. Utensils and straws are biodegradable. There are also no bags given to hold your meal.  The servers were patient and helpful towards me as it was my first time trying sweetgreen. He explained to me some popular options and how create your own works. As well as giving me some recommendations for my own order.  I definitely would recommend others to give it a try however it is far too healthy and expensive for me. Ordering a Create Your Own Salad cost me roughly $14.

Apparently food gets "stolen" here if you order delivery. The order that i was suppost to pick up got "stolen" twice. Both times i tried to pick up they said they were remaking it. I dont know if it was a fellow postmate or another delivery guy but It made me waste an hour of my 8 delivery bonus before 9pm. Not only did it do this but at the time, i already had an order for someone from another place and that order ended up being affected. They put pick up items on this pick up wall and then just leave it unsupervised. The staff here does NOT check order names or numbers. Anyone can come in staring into their phone and just grab any order.  Edit: I changed my rating all the way down to a 1 star because this is a severe problem that makes not only me look bad as a postmate, but this makes postmates look bad and decrease the likelihood of people choosing postmates. Not only did I not make the 8 deliveries before 9pm for my bonus, but I got a penalty on my account that temporarily blocked me from getting deliveries with a warning of more severe penalties.

Two stars for this location. Generally, this franchise is pretty good but this one needs improvement. One, store NEEDS a clear sign where the line starts, being it was my first time in that location I just followed where the others are lining up. I wasn’t the only one unclear about the line, as new customers walking in did the same mistake. Second, the staff could be more knowledgeable about their products... thus, will avoid misunderstandings in the future. LASTLY,  cleanliness can be improved immensely. Coming from the industry as a chef, I can tell there was a lack of caution to sanitary stations... it wasn’t even rush hours. That being said, my father did not eat his $14 salad.
